{{Infobox football match | title = 2007 Turkish Cup Final | image = | event = [[Türkiye Kupası 2006–07]] | team1 = [[Beşiktaş J.K.]] | team1association = | team1score = 1 | team2 = [[Kayseri Erciyesspor]] | team2association = | team2score = 0 | details = After [[extra time]]. | date = May 9, 2007 | stadium = [[İzmir Atatürk Stadium]] | city = [[Izmir]] | man_of_the_match1a = [[Deivson Rogerio da Silva|Bobo]] ([[Beşiktaş J.K.]]) | referee = [[İsmet Arzuman]] ([[Turkish Football Federation|Turkey]]) | attendance = | weather = Fine | previous = [[2006 Turkish Cup Final|2006]] | next = [[2008 Turkish Cup Final|2008]] }}
The '''2007 Turkish Cup Final''' was a [[Association Football|football]] match between [[Beşiktaş J.K.]] and [[Kayseri Erciyesspor]]. The match was played at the [[İzmir Atatürk Stadium]] for the 2nd time in a row. Beşiktaş won 1–0 after extra time.
==Beşiktaş J.K.== As the defending Turkish Cup champions, Beşiktaş finished 2nd place in Group D, to proceed to the Quarter Finals. Beşiktaş beat [[Vestel Manisaspor]] 4-0 at home, and lost 0–2 away. In the Semi Finals Beşiktaş faced off, with one of their Istanbul rivals, [[Fenerbahçe S.K.]]. At home, Beşiktaş won 1–0. Away Beşiktaş ended the match down 1–0. In extra time though, [[Mert Nobre]] scored a goal for Beşiktaş making it 1–1. Beşiktaş continued on to the Final.
==Kayseri Erciyesspor== Kayseri Erciyesspor finished 2nd place in Group A. In the Quarter Finals they faced [[Galatasaray S.K. (football team)|Galatasaray]]. The 1st match ended 0–0 at home, and away 1-1. Kayseri Erciyes won by away goals. In the Semi Finals, Kayseri Erciyes faced [[Trabzonspor]]. The results were a 1–0 win away and a 1–1 draw at home. Kayseri Erciyes managed to 5–4 in the penalties, and proceed to the Final.
==Final== The game ended 0–0 after 90 minutes. During extra time [[Deivson Rogerio da Silva|Bobo]] scored the only goal of the game. Beşiktaş won their 7th Turkish Cup, and their second in a row.
