'''Cuban Cricket Commission''' is the official [[Sport governing body|governing body]] of the sport of [[cricket]] in [[Cuba]]. Its current headquarters is in [[Havana]], [[Cuba]]. The Commission was granted [[List of International Cricket Council members#Affiliate Members|affiliate membership]] of the [[International Cricket Council]] (ICC) in 2002, but had its membership revoked in 2013 for failing to "demonstrate a suitable administrative structure to conduct its affairs" under ICC guidelines. The organisation has previously been invited to field teams in [[ICC Americas]]-sanctioned tournaments (most notably the [[2010 ICC Americas Championship Division Four]]), but it is unclear if it is (or was) a member of that association.

