The '''Indian Powerlifting Federation''' is a national governing body for the sport of [[powerlifting]] as recognized by the [[Ministry of Youth Affairs and Sports]], [[Government of India]] as well as The [[Indian Olympic Association]]. Currently, it has more than 10,000 (ten thousand) Powerlifter members, both Men & Women. It also has 37 affiliated State Association and 6 Central Govt. Office Board Units.<ref>{{cite web|title=Welcome To Indian Powerlifting Federation|url=http://www.indianpowerliftingfederation.com/index.php|website=Indianpowerliftingfederation|publisher=Indian Powerlifting Federation|accessdate=8 June 2016}}</ref>
==Events== The Indian Powerlifting Federation is organizing the Asian Powerlifting Championships 2016, which is to be held from 7 June 2016 to 12 June 2016 in [[Udaipur]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Calendar of Events 2016-2018|url=http://powerlifting-asia.com/2016/01/20/asian-powerlifting-championships-2016/|website=powerlifting-asia.com|publisher=GeneratePress|accessdate=8 June 2016}}</ref>
==External links== *[http://www.indianpowerliftingfederation.com/index.php Official Indian Powerlifting web site]
