{{Infobox UK Racecourse | Name = Salisbury | Image = [[Image:Salisbury racecourse.jpg|220px]] | Caption = | Website = http://www.salisburyracecourse.co.uk | Location = [[Salisbury]], [[Wiltshire]] | Owner = | Opened = | Channel = [[Racing UK]] | CourseType = [[Flat racing|Flat]] | NotableRaces = [[Sovereign Stakes]] | Prev = [[Ripon Racecourse|Ripon]] | Next = [[Sandown Park Racecourse|Sandown Park]] }}
'''Salisbury Racecourse''' is a [[Flat racing|flat racecourse]] in the United Kingdom featuring [[thoroughbred horse racing]], {{convert|3|mi|km|0}} southwest of [[Salisbury]], [[Wiltshire]], England. Fifteen race meetings a year are held there between early May and mid-October.
==History== There has been racing at the race course located three miles from Salisbury since the mid-16th century. Many great horses have won at the track, including [[Gimcrack]] (1768), [[Eclipse (horse)|Eclipse]] (1769), [[Sun Chariot (horse)|Sun Chariot]] (1941),<ref name=Glueckstein>{{cite book|author=Glueckstein, Fred|title=Churchill and Colonist II: The Story of Winston Churchill and His Famous Race Horse|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=5kTiBQAAQBAJ&pg=PT25 |year=2014|publisher=iUniverse |isbn=978-1-4917-4973-9 |pages=25–}}</ref> [[Mill Reef]] (1970) and [[Brigadier Gerard (horse)|Brigadier Gerard]] (1970). [[Sir Percy]], winner of the 2006 Derby, and [[Look Here (horse)|Look Here]], winner of the 2008 Oaks, had both won at Salisbury the previous year.<ref name=Guide/> [[Jockey]] [[Lester Piggott]] first rode in public at Salisbury when he was aged twelve; that was in 1948 when he was an apprentice jockey and weighed just five stone.<ref name=Guide/> American jockey [[Steve Cauthen]] made his British debut at the course in 1979 when he rode Marquee Universal to victory here.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.independent.co.uk/sport/racing-cauthen-finds-bluegrass-is-greener-1183121.html|title=Racing: Cauthen finds bluegrass is greener|last=Richard Edmondson|date=6 November 1998|work=The Independent|accessdate=2 September 2016}}</ref>
It was here in 1949 that [[Winston Churchill]] first raced his Colonist II in the one mile Upavon Stakes. The horse won, and went on to win the [[Ribblesdale Stakes]] at Ascot later that year.<ref name=Glueckstein/>
==The racecourse== About sixteen race meetings take place at Salisbury Racecourse each year between early May and mid-October. It is a downland flat-racing course with no jumps. There is a mix of race types with the majority being handicaps, where horses of similar ability race against each other, and maidens, where horses which have yet to win a race compete. The course is also renowned for its races for two-year-olds, and many of these young horses have gone on to achieve great things.<ref name=Guide>{{cite web |url=http://www.salisburyracecourse.co.uk/salisburyracecourse/visiting/faqs.html |title=Racegoers Guide |publisher=Salisbury Racecourse |accessdate=2 September 2016}}</ref>
==Notable races== {| class = "sortable" | border="1" cellpadding="0" style="border-collapse: collapse; font-size:90%" |- bgcolor="#77dd77" align="center" ! style="width:70px" |Month ! style="width:80px" |DOW ! Race Name ! style="width:60px" |Type ! style="width:70px" | '''Grade''' ! style="width:80px" |Distance ! style="width:50px" |Age/Sex |- | style="text-align:center" |{{Sort|1|June}} | style="text-align:center" |Sunday | [[Cathedral Stakes]] | style="text-align:center" |Flat | style="text-align:center" | Listed | style="text-align:center" |{{Sort|1207|6f }} | style="text-align:center" |3yo + |- | style="text-align:center" |{{Sort|2|August}} | style="text-align:center" |Wednesday | [[Upavon Fillies' Stakes]] | style="text-align:center" |Flat | style="text-align:center" | Listed | style="text-align:center" |{{Sort|1992|1m 1f 198y }} | style="text-align:center" |3yo + |- | style="text-align:center" |{{Sort|3|August}} | style="text-align:center" |Thursday | [[Sovereign Stakes]] | style="text-align:center" |Flat | style="text-align:center" | Group 3 | style="text-align:center" |{{Sort|1609|1m }} | style="text-align:center" |3yo + |- | style="text-align:center" |{{Sort|4|September}} | style="text-align:center" |Thursday | [[Dick Poole Fillies' Stakes]] | style="text-align:center" |Flat | style="text-align:center" | Group 3 | style="text-align:center" |{{Sort|1207|6f }} | style="text-align:center" |2yo only f |}
;Other races * [[Stonehenge Stakes]]
Salisbury's earliest big race was the King's Plate for 6-year-olds, awarded by [[George I of Great Britain|George I]] in 1723.<ref>{{cite book |last=Whyte |first=James Christie |authorlink= |title=History of the British turf, from the earliest period to the present day, Volume I |url=http://openlibrary.org/books/OL6544990M/History_of_the_British_turf |accessdate=1 May 2013 |year=1840 |publisher=H. Colburn |location=[[London]] |isbn= |page=402}}</ref>
