{{Infobox MMA event |name=UFC Fight Night: Maia vs. Usman |image=UFC Fight Night Usman vs. Ponzinibbio event poster.jpg |promotion=[[Ultimate Fighting Championship]] |date= {{start date|2018|05|19}} |venue=[[Movistar Arena]] |city= [[Santiago]], [[Chile]] |attendance= 11,082<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://mmajunkie.com/2018/05/ufc-fight-night-129-attendance-chilean-debut-draws-announced-11082-fans|title=UFC Fight Night 129 attendance: Chilean debut draws announced 11,082 fans|publisher=mmajunkie.com|author=Staff|date=2018-05-20|access-date=2018-05-20}}</ref> |live gate= |previousevent= [[UFC 224|UFC 224: Nunes vs. Pennington]] |followingevent= [[UFC Fight Night: Thompson vs. Till]] }}
'''''UFC Fight Night: Maia vs. Usman''''' (also known as '''''UFC Fight Night 129''''') was a [[mixed martial arts]] event produced by the [[Ultimate Fighting Championship]] that was held on May 19, 2018, at [[Movistar Arena]] in [[Santiago]], [[Chile]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.express.co.uk/sport/ufc/900713/Next-UFC-Event-2018-Fight-Schedule|title=Next UFCevent: full schedule of UFC events for 2018|publisher=express.co.uk|author=Chisanga Malata|date=2018-02-10|accessdate=2018-02-10}}</ref>
==Background== The event marked the promotion's first visit to Chile.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://redgol.cl/2017/12/fight-ufc-tiene-reservado-el-movistar-aren/|title=Fight! UFC has reserved the Movistar Arena to present on May 19 in Chile|publisher=redgol.cl|author=Felipe Kaponi|date=2017-12-19|accessdate=2018-01-31}} {{es icon}}</ref>
A welterweight bout between [[The Ultimate Fighter: American Top Team vs. Blackzilians|The Ultimate Fighter: American Top Team vs. Blackzilians]] welterweight winner [[Kamaru Usman]] and [[Santiago Ponzinibbio]] was expected to serve as the event headliner.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://mmajunkie.com/2018/03/kamaru-usman-vs-santiago-ponzinibbio-official-for-ufc-fight-night-129-headliner|title=Kamaru Usman vs. Santiago Ponzinibbio official for UFC Fight Night 129 headliner|publisher=mmajunkie.com|author=Staff|date=2018-03-24|accessdate=2018-03-26}}</ref> However, Ponzinibbio pulled out on April 21 due to injury.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://mmajunkie.com/2018/04/ufc-chile-main-headliners-fall-apart-santiago-ponzinibbio-volkan-oezdemir-out|title=UFC Chile main, co-main events fall apart with Santiago Ponzinibbio, Volkan Oezdemir out|publisher=mmajunkie.com|author=Mike Bohn|date=2018-04-21|accessdate=2018-04-21}}</ref> He was replaced by former [[UFC Welterweight Championship|UFC Welterweight]] and [[UFC Middleweight Championship|Middleweight Championship]] challenger [[Demian Maia]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://sportv.globo.com/site/combate/noticia/ultimate-encaminha-demian-como-substituto-de-ponzinibbio-no-ufc-chile.ghtml|title=Ultimate announces Demian Maia as substitute for Ponzinibbio at UFC Chile|publisher=sportv.globo.com|author=Raphael Marinho|date=2018-04-26|accessdate=2018-04-26}} {{pt icon}}</ref>
A flyweight bout between former [[UFC Flyweight Championship]] challenger [[Ray Borg]] and [[Brandon Moreno]] was originally expected to take place at [[UFC Fight Night: Cowboy vs. Medeiros]]. However, due to a minor injury sustained by Moreno, the pairing was postponed and rescheduled to take place at [[UFC 223]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.mmafighting.com/2018/1/31/16957586/injury-postpones-ray-borg-vs-brandon-moreno-to-ufc-223-in-brooklyn|title=Injury postpones Ray Borg vs. Brandon Moreno to UFC 223 in Brooklyn|publisher=mmafighting.com|author=Danny Segura|date=2018-01-31|accessdate=2018-01-31}}</ref> The bout was delayed again, after Borg had issues related to glass shards in his eye as a result of the former [[UFC Featherweight Championship|UFC Featherweight]] and [[UFC Lightweight Championship|Lightweight Champion]] [[Conor McGregor]] and crew [[UFC 223#Conor McGregor and team assault on bus|bus melee]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.mmafighting.com/2018/4/5/17204860/ray-borg-vs-brandon-moreno-pulled-from-ufc-223-in-latest-conor-mcgregor-incident-casualty|title=Ray Borg vs. Brandon Moreno pulled from UFC 223 in latest Conor McGregor incident casualty|publisher=mmafighting.com|author=Dave Doyle|date=2018-04-05|accessdate=2018-04-06}}</ref> The pairing was scheduled again and was expected to take place at this event.<ref name="takethree">{{cite news|url=https://www.mmafighting.com/2018/4/11/17226020/ray-borg-vs-brandon-moreno-rebooked-for-ufc-chile|title=Ray Borg vs. Brandon Moreno rebooked for UFC Chile |publisher=mmafighting.com|author=Danny Segura|date=2018-04-11|accessdate=2018-04-11}}</ref> However, Borg withdrew from the bout to take care of his child, who required brain surgery.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.mmafighting.com/2018/4/27/17292294/ray-borg-withdraws-from-ufc-chile-bout-vs-brandon-moreno-due-to-childs-surgery|title=Ray Borg withdraws from UFC Chile bout vs. Brandon Moreno due to child’s surgery|publisher=mmafighting.com|author=Alexander K. Lee|date=2018-04-27|access-date=2018-04-28}}</ref> He was replaced by [[Alexandre Pantoja]].<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://sportv.globo.com/site/combate/noticia/alexandre-pantoja-substitui-ray-borg-em-luta-contra-brandon-moreno-no-ufc-santiago.ghtml|title=Alexandre Pantoja replaces Ray Borg in bout against Brandon Moreno at UFC Santiago|publisher=sportv.globo.com|author=Raphael Marinho|date=2018-04-28|access-date=2018-04-29}} {{pt icon}}</ref>
A light heavyweight bout between former [[UFC Light Heavyweight Championship|UFC Light Heavyweight Champion]] [[Maurício Rua]] and former title challenger [[Volkan Oezdemir]] was expected to take place at this event. However, it was reported on April 13, 2018, that Oezdemir was pulled from the event due to alleged [[visa (document)|visa]] issues stemming from a previous legal transgression, restricting his travel to Chile.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://sportv.globo.com/site/combate/noticia/oezdemir-e-impedido-de-deixar-os-eua-e-luta-com-shogun-no-ufc-chile-e-cancelada.ghtml|title=Oezdemir is forbidden to leave the US and the Shogun bout will be rescheduled|publisher=sportv.globo.com|author=Marcelo Barone and Raphael Marinho|date=2018-03-13|accessdate=2018-03-13}} {{pt icon}}</ref> The pairing was left intact and rescheduled for July 22, 2018, at [[UFC Fight Night: Volkan vs. Shogun]].<ref name="Hamburg">{{cite news|url=http://mmajunkie.com/2018/04/volkan-oezdemir-mauricio-shogun-rua-rebooked-headline-ufc-fight-night-134-hamburg|title=Volkan Oezdemir vs. 'Shogun' rebooked, now headlines UFC Fight Night 134 in Hamburg|publisher=mmajunkie.com|author=Staff|date=2018-04-23|accessdate=2018-04-23}}</ref>
